              Hello, and welcome to the Samurai guild!
-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

I, Acer, as the GM of the Samurai am glad to have you with us. As you will
soon find out in these docs, you've just joined one of the most unique and
different guilds in Darkwind.

The Samurai is a warrior from cultures based on the medieval Japanese civil-
ization. He lives by a very strict code of honor and behavior, called...
Bushido (or it translates to "The Way of the Warrior"). This code demands:

       1.) Honor is above everything.
       2.) Absolute obedience to his/her lord.
       3.) Readiness to die for honor or for his lord at any time.
       4.) Eagerness to avenge any dishonor to his lord, his family, or himself.
       5.) Willingness to repay all debts honorably.
       6.) And, most important, the unwillingness to demonstrate the most
           dishonorable trait - Cowardice.

As you have probably already found out, within the Samurai guild are three
families or houses. Each one headed by a player GM, or a Lord. This person
has the ability to promote/demote you in rank, issue/take from you honor,
or to banish you from the house and from the Samurai all together. As you 
can see, you MUST treat the Lord with honor and respect he/she is due. And
as you can probably see, the Samurai guild makes for some great roleplaying
if you choose to do so.



See also: 'commands', 'skills', 'houses' and 'emotes'.
Syntax: shelp <topic>
